30|$|VIMS {{spectra of}} the changed regions {{agree that they}} are {{inconsistent}} with clouds. At the top of Figure 20, we show spectra of the changed and unchanged parts of Hetpet Regio and compare them to the spectrum of a cloud from the T 33 flyby (2007 June 29). As {{is evident from the}} figure, the brightening in Hetpet Regio occurred exclusively within the <b>atmospheric</b> <b>windows</b> to the surface. In particular, at the spectral wings of the <b>atmospheric</b> <b>windows,</b> where clouds in the upper troposphere show distinctive and significant brightening over surface features (arrows in Figure 20), the changed region is static, as would be expected if it were purely a surface phenomenon. Griffith [43] and others have used similar altitude discriminators, particularly at the longward end of the 2 -micron window.|$|R
