40|$|It {{is often}} {{assumed that the}} {{atmosphere}} is non-dispersive to millimeter and submillimeter wavelength radiation, so the dierential atmospheric phase of an interferometer varies linearly with frequency. Up to about 300 GHz, this is approximately true. However, near absorption lines, {{and especially in the}} sub-millimeter wavelength <b>atmospheric</b> <b>windows</b> where the absorption lines are very strong and always near, the assumption of a non-disperive atmosphere breaks down markedly...|$|R
